	<ext_description linkend="Classification_assignment_mim.applied_classification_assignment">
An <b>applied_classification_assignment</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="management_resources_schema:ir_express:management_resources_schema.classification_assignment"/> that associates an instance of <express_ref linkend="group_schema:ir_express:group_schema.group"/> or of one of its specializations with one or more <express_ref linkend="classification_assignment:mim:Classification_assignment_mim.classification_item"/> instances for classification purposes.
<p>The considered group is specified with the inherited attribute <express_ref linkend="management_resources_schema:ir_express:management_resources_schema.classification_assignment.assigned_class"/>.</p>
		<note number="1">The considered group may be a <express_ref linkend="classification_schema:ir_express:classification_schema.class"/> or a <express_ref linkend="product_property_definition_schema:ir_express:product_property_definition_schema.characterized_object"/>.</note>
		<note number="2">Specific application modules address particular kinds of classification.</note>
		<example>The entity <express_ref linkend="security_classification:mim:Security_classification_mim.applied_security_classification_assignment"/> will be used in order to represent confidentiality level classification.</example>
		<p>The meaning of the association is specified with the inherited attribute role.</p>
		<p>Where applicable, the following value of classification role name shall be used:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>'reference': the items to which the classification assignment applies, are by intent incompletely transferred.</li>
		</ul>
		<note number="3">This value can be used when assembly data are exchanged iteratively between two partners, to avoid to send twice the CAD files that contain the geometric representation of each component.</note>
	</ext_description>
	<!-- 
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
   Schema: Classification_assignment_mim  Entity: applied_classification_assignment  Attribute: items 
   <express_ref linkend="classification_assignment:mim:Classification_assignment_mim.applied_classification_assignment.items"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ 
  -->
	<ext_description linkend="Classification_assignment_mim.applied_classification_assignment.items">
the set of one or more instances of types listed in <express_ref linkend="classification_assignment:mim:Classification_assignment_mim.classification_item"/>, that are associated with the classification information.
</ext_description>
